            . I live with James Faulker; he <rs id="t18170521-130-viclabel667" type="occupation">keeps the King of Denmark public-house</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170521-130-victim782 t18170521-130-viclabel667"></join>. On the 2d of May we lost the spoons.</p>
               <p>THOMAS BURLTON. I am a pawnbroker. On the 3d of May I bought the spoons of the prisoner, for 7s. 6d. I am sure he is the man.</p>
               <p>ROBERT COOMBS. I received information that the spoons had been stolen, and found them at Burlton's, who said he bought them of the prisoner. I went to him, he said he bought the duplicate for 1s. 6d., redeemed them, and sold them to Burlton.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I took them out of pledge.</p>
               <p>
